  "title": "MemoryStore",
  "description": "In-memory KeyValueStore backed by a `Map`. Holds values **by reference** — no cloning, no serialization — so it accepts any value but does not persist across sessions and does not isolate the caller from later mutation of a stored object. Ideal for tests and ephemeral data, and as a drop-in store when persistence is not needed.",
